## Detailed Implementation Plan: Share Profile Feature

### Overview

This plan adds a "Share Profile" feature mirroring the existing post share architecture. It involves three pieces: (1) two new server-side routes for OG meta HTML and dynamic OG image generation, (2) a client-side utility for building the share URL, and (3) a share button in both `ProfileHeroSection` (own profile) and `VisitProfile` (visited profiles) that reuses the existing `ShareMenu` component.

---

### Part 1: Server-Side Routes (in `server/server.js`)

Both routes should be added **directly above the existing `/share/post/:journalId/image` route** (line 447), following the exact same structural pattern.

#### 1A. Profile Share Image Route: `GET /share/u/:username/image`

This route generates a composite 1200x630 JPEG. Unlike the post share image route (which simply resizes a single upstream image), this one must composite multiple elements: background, avatar, text.

**Data flow:**

1. Import `getUserByUsernameService` from `./services/getUserDataService.js` at the top of `server.js` (line ~9)
2. Extract `username` from `req.params`
3. Call `getUserByUsernameService(username)` to get user data
4. On error (user not found), redirect 302 to `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_URL`

**Image generation strategy using Sharp + SVG overlay:**

Sharp cannot natively render text, but it supports compositing SVG buffers. The approach is:

**Step A - Create the 1200x630 base layer:**

```js
// If user has backgroundImage url, fetch and resize it
// If user has gradient, render an SVG rect with the gradient
// If neither, use a default dark background

let baseImage;

const bgData = userData.background;
if (bgData?.backgroundImage) {
    // Extract URL from "url(...)" pattern
    const urlMatch = bgData.backgroundImage.match(/url\(["']?([^"')]+)["']?\)/);
    if (urlMatch?.[1]) {
        const evaluation = evaluateShareImageCandidate(urlMatch[1]);
        if (evaluation.ok) {
            const remote = await fetchRemoteImageBuffer(evaluation.resolvedUrl);
            baseImage = await sharp(remote.buffer, { limitInputPixels: 60_000_000 })
                .rotate()
                .resize(1200, 630, { fit: 'cover' })
                .toBuffer();
        }
    }
}

if (!baseImage && bgData?.backgroundImage?.includes('linear-gradient')) {
    // Parse gradient and render as SVG
    baseImage = Buffer.from(`<svg width="1200" height="630">
        <defs><linearGradient id="g" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
            <!-- parse gradient stops -->
        </linearGradient></defs>
        <rect width="1200" height="630" fill="url(#g)"/>
    </svg>`);
    baseImage = await sharp(baseImage).png().toBuffer();
}

if (!baseImage) {
    // Default: dark gradient fallback
    const fallbackSvg = Buffer.from(
        `<svg width="1200" height="630">
            <rect width="1200" height="630" fill="#1a1a2e"/>
        </svg>`
    );
    baseImage = await sharp(fallbackSvg).png().toBuffer();
}
```

**Step B - Prepare circular avatar:**

```js
let avatarComposite = null;
if (userData.image_url) {
    const avatarEval = evaluateShareImageCandidate(userData.image_url);
    if (avatarEval.ok) {
        const avatarRemote = await fetchRemoteImageBuffer(avatarEval.resolvedUrl);
        const avatarSize = 180;
        const avatarBuffer = await sharp(avatarRemote.buffer, { limitInputPixels: 60_000_000 })
            .rotate()
            .resize(avatarSize, avatarSize, { fit: 'cover' })
            .toBuffer();

        // Create circular mask
        const circleMask = Buffer.from(
            `<svg width="${avatarSize}" height="${avatarSize}">
                <circle cx="${avatarSize / 2}" cy="${avatarSize / 2}" r="${avatarSize / 2}" fill="white"/>
            </svg>`
        );

        const circularAvatar = await sharp(avatarBuffer)
            .composite([{
                input: circleMask,
                blend: 'dest-in',
            }])
            .png()
            .toBuffer();

        avatarComposite = {
            input: circularAvatar,
            top: 140,     // vertically centered roughly
            left: 510,    // horizontally centered: (1200 - 180) / 2
        };
    }
}
```

**Step C - Create text overlay as SVG:**

The text overlay is an SVG buffer composited on top. This approach avoids font rendering issues since SVG text is natively supported by Sharp (via librsvg).

```js
const displayName = normalizeWhitespace(userData.name) || 'Anonymous';
const usernameText = userData.username ? `@${userData.username}` : '';
const bioText = toPreviewText(userData.bio || '', 120);

// Escape for SVG
const svgEsc = (str) => String(str)
    .replace(/&/g, '&amp;')
    .replace(/</g, '&lt;')
    .replace(/>/g, '&gt;')
    .replace(/"/g, '&quot;');

const textSvg = Buffer.from(`<svg width="1200" height="630" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <style>
        .name { fill: white; font-size: 42px; font-weight: 700; font-family: sans-serif; }
        .handle { fill: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); font-size: 24px; font-family: sans-serif; }
        .bio { fill: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); font-size: 22px; font-family: sans-serif; }
        .brand { fill: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 18px; font-family: sans-serif; }
    </style>
    <text x="600" y="370" text-anchor="middle" class="name">${svgEsc(displayName)}</text>
    ${usernameText ? `<text x="600" y="405" text-anchor="middle" class="handle">${svgEsc(usernameText)}</text>` : ''}
    ${bioText ? `<text x="600" y="450" text-anchor="middle" class="bio">${svgEsc(bioText)}</text>` : ''}
    <text x="600" y="600" text-anchor="middle" class="brand">iskrib.com</text>
</svg>`);
```

**Step D - Composite everything and output:**

```js
// Add a semi-transparent dark overlay for text readability
const darkOverlay = Buffer.from(
    `<svg width="1200" height="630">
        <rect width="1200" height="630" fill="rgba(0,0,0,0.4)"/>
    </svg>`
);

const composites = [
    { input: await sharp(darkOverlay).png().toBuffer(), top: 0, left: 0 },
];
if (avatarComposite) composites.push(avatarComposite);
composites.push({ input: textSvg, top: 0, left: 0 });

const ogImage = await sharp(baseImage)
    .resize(1200, 630, { fit: 'cover' })
    .composite(composites)
    .jpeg({ quality: 82, mozjpeg: true })
    .toBuffer();

res.set('Content-Type', 'image/jpeg');
res.set('Cache-Control', 'public, max-age=3600');
return res.send(ogImage);
```

**Error handling:** Wrap entirely in try/catch. On any failure, redirect 302 to `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_URL` (identical pattern to line 476 of the post image route).

**Gradient parsing helper function:** Create a helper `parseGradientToSvg(bgData, width, height)` that handles two background types:
- If `bgData.backgroundImage` contains `linear-gradient(...)`, parse the angle and color stops, and return an SVG string with a `<linearGradient>` element
- If `bgData.background` is a solid hex color, return `<rect fill="${color}"/>`

The gradient format from `profileGradients.js` (line 6 of that file) is:
```
linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(42, 123, 155, 1) 0%, rgba(87, 199, 133, 1) 50%, rgba(237, 221, 83, 1) 100%)
```

A regex can extract the angle and stops:
```js
const parseLinearGradient = (gradientStr) => {
    const match = gradientStr.match(/linear-gradient\((\d+)deg,\s*(.+)\)/);
    if (!match) return null;
    const angle = parseInt(match[1], 10);
    const stopsRaw = match[2];
    // Parse each "rgba(...) N%" stop
    const stops = [...stopsRaw.matchAll(/rgba?\(([^)]+)\)\s+(\d+)%/g)]
        .map(m => ({
            color: `rgba(${m[1]})`,
            offset: `${m[2]}%`,
        }));
    return { angle, stops };
};
```

Then convert angle to SVG `x1,y1,x2,y2` coordinates (90deg = left-to-right: x1=0%,y1=0%,x2=100%,y2=0%).

#### 1B. Profile Share HTML Route: `GET /share/u/:username`

This is structurally identical to the post share route (lines 530-586) but for profiles.

```js
app.get('/share/u/:username', async (req, res) => {
    const { username } = req.params;
    const shareOrigin = getRequestOrigin(req);
    const profileUrl = `${SITE_URL}/u/${encodeURIComponent(username)}`;

    try {
        const { userData } = await getUserByUsernameService(username);
        const user = userData[0];
        if (!user) {
            return res.redirect(302, profileUrl);
        }

        const displayName = normalizeWhitespace(user.name) || 'Anonymous';
        const title = `${displayName}'s Profile | Iskryb`;
        const description = toPreviewText(
            user.bio || `View ${displayName}'s journals and opinions on Iskryb`
        );
        const shareImageUrl = new URL(
            `/share/u/${encodeURIComponent(username)}/image`,
            `${shareOrigin}/`
        ).toString();
        const fbAppIdTag = META_FB_APP_ID
            ? `<meta property="fb:app_id" content="${escHtml(META_FB_APP_ID)}">`
            : '';

        const html = `<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>${escHtml(title)}</title>
<meta name="description" content="${escHtml(description)}">
${fbAppIdTag}
<link rel="canonical" href="${escHtml(profileUrl)}">
<meta property="og:type" content="profile">
<meta property="og:title" content="${escHtml(title)}">
<meta property="og:description" content="${escHtml(description)}">
<meta property="og:image" content="${escHtml(shareImageUrl)}">
<meta property="og:image:width" content="${String(DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_WIDTH)}">
<meta property="og:image:height" content="${String(DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_HEIGHT)}">
<meta property="og:url" content="${escHtml(profileUrl)}">
<meta property="og:site_name" content="Iskryb">
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
<meta name="twitter:title" content="${escHtml(title)}">
<meta name="twitter:description" content="${escHtml(description)}">
<meta name="twitter:image" content="${escHtml(shareImageUrl)}">
<meta name="twitter:image:width" content="${String(DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_WIDTH)}">
<meta name="twitter:image:height" content="${String(DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE_HEIGHT)}">
<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=${escHtml(profileUrl)}">
<script>
window.location.replace(${JSON.stringify(profileUrl)});
</script>
</head>
<body>
<p>${escHtml(displayName)} - Redirecting to Iskryb...</p>
<a href="${escHtml(profileUrl)}">Click here if not redirected</a>
</body>
</html>`;

        res.set('Content-Type', 'text/html; charset=utf-8');
        return res.send(html);
    } catch (err) {
        console.error('share profile route error:', err?.message || err);
        return res.redirect(302, profileUrl);
    }
});
```

Key differences from the post share route:
- `og:type` is `"profile"` not `"article"`
- Adds `<meta http-equiv="refresh">` as a non-JS fallback (matching the requirement)
- The user data comes from `getUserByUsernameService` not `getShareJournal`

